Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 3-19-2025

Thank you for using redditStories ("the App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our services.

1. Information We Collect

We do not collect personally identifiable information unless explicitly provided by you.

The App may collect anonymous usage data for analytics purposes.

If the App integrates with TikTok, we may receive basic user data as permitted by TikTok's API policies.

2. How We Use Your Information

To provide and improve the functionality of the App.

To analyze usage trends and improve user experience.

We do not sell or share your data with third parties.

3. Data Security

We take reasonable security measures to protect user data.

However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.

4. Third-Party Services

The App may interact with TikTok's services, and their privacy policy governs their data usage.

We are not responsible for third-party privacy practices.

5. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically.

Continued use of the App after changes implies acceptance of the new terms.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions, contact us at jackvz23@yahoo.com.
